Certainly! Below is a simple Java game where the user has to guess a random number between 0 and 10. The game provides feedback on whether the guess is too high, too low, or correct.

```java
import java.util.Random;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class NumberGuessingGame {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Random random = new Random();
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        int randomNumber = random.nextInt(11); // Generates a random number between 0 and 10
        int userGuess = -1; // Initialize with a number out of range

        System.out.println("Welcome to the Number Guessing Game!");
        System.out.println("I have randomly selected a number between 0 and 10.");
        System.out.println("Try to guess the number!");

        while (userGuess != randomNumber) {
            System.out.print("Enter your guess: ");
            if (scanner.hasNextInt()) {
                userGuess = scanner.nextInt();

                if (userGuess < 0 || userGuess > 10) {
                    System.out.println("Please enter a number between 0 and 10.");
                } else if (userGuess < randomNumber) {
                    System.out.println("Too low! Try again.");
                } else if (userGuess > randomNumber) {
                    System.out.println("Too high! Try again.");
                } else {
                    System.out.println("Congratulations! You guessed the correct number: " + randomNumber);
                }
            } else {
                System.out.println("Invalid input. Please enter a number between 0 and 10.");
                scanner.next(); // Clear invalid input
            }
        }

        scanner.close();
    }
}
```

### How to Run the Game:
1. **Compile the Program**: Save the code in a file named `NumberGuessingGame.java`. Open a terminal or command prompt, navigate to the directory containing the file, and compile it using:
   ```
   javac NumberGuessingGame.java
   ```

2. **Run the Compiled Program**: After successful compilation, run the program using:
   ```
   java NumberGuessingGame
   ```

3. **Play the Game**: Follow the on-screen instructions to guess the number. The program will provide feedback after each guess until you correctly guess the number.

Enjoy playing the game!
